			<div class="text-left lap-text-left tab-text-center mob-text-center">
				<div class="description ">
                	<p><span class="p--large">NVIDIA is bringing <a href="/glossary/generative-physical-ai/">physical AI</a>&nbsp;to the automotive industry, connecting vehicles, factories, and digital worlds through AI and <a href="/use-cases/autonomous-vehicle-simulation/">simulation</a>. With&nbsp;<a href="/solutions/ai/">NVIDIA AI</a>, <a href="/omniverse/">Omniverse™</a>, and <a href="/data-center/solutions/accelerated-computing/">accelerated computing</a>, automakers are using AI physics, generative AI, and interactive <a href="/glossary/digital-twin/">digital twins</a> to accelerate design and engineering, optimize factory operations, and validate autonomous driving systems in simulation before deployment. The result is faster development, safer vehicles, and more efficient production.</span></p>
